        <li><strong>Upside:</strong> Structural shifts causing permanently higher interest rate volatility, driving immense volume through CME's Treasury and SOFR complex.</li>
        <li><strong>Upside:</strong> Stronger pricing power execution than modeled, where CME successfully raises exchange fees above inflation without losing market share.</li>
        <li><strong>Downside:</strong> A prolonged period of low market volatility and flat interest rates (ZIRP-like conditions), leading to stagnant or declining trading volumes.</li>
        <li><strong>Downside:</strong> Regulatory changes or the rise of decentralized finance (DeFi) alternatives that threaten traditional exchange moats, though regulatory capture makes this difficult.</li>
      </ul>

